ussions and commemoration. This richly illustrated and thought-provoking book reinstates Hill 70 to its rightful place among the pantheon of battles that helped forge the reputation of the famed Canadian Corps during the First World War, and it sheds new light on the key role played by Lieutenant-General Sir Arthur Currie, who fought his first major action as commander of the Canadian Corps.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xCampaignszFrance. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xRegimental historieszCanada. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War I.2bisacsh1 aCook, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelaney, Douglas E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelaney, Douglas E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDurflinger, Serge Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDurflinger, Serge Marc, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEngen, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoley, Robert T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGardner, Nikolas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGranatstein, J.L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHumphries, Mark Osborne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIarocci, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311141795040uhttps://doi